headline: US States Likely to Defy US Downgrade to Keep Top Credit Ratings
summary: (Bloomberg) -- US states from Florida to North Carolina and Texas would likely hold onto top-notch credit scores from Moody’s Ratings, mostly because they’re in better fiscal shape than the federal government itself.
